0. REQUIREMENTS

This program has tested on environment configuration

    Linux Fedora 26
    Android Studio 4.0.1
    Android 7.1.1

In Android Studio you should check following settings

    Select menu `Tools'.
    Select submenu `SDK Manager'.
    Select tab `SDK Platforms'.

There should be installed

    Android SDK Platform 30
    Android SDK Platform 29
    Sources for Android 29
    Android SDK Platform 28
    Sources for Android 28

In Android Studio you should check following settings

    Select menu `Tools'.
    Select submenu `SDK Manager'.
    Select tab `SDK Tools'.

There should be installed

    Android SDK Build-Tools 30.0.1
    Android SDK Build-Tools 29.0.2
    Android SDK Build-Tools 28.0.2

1. CONFIGURATION

No configuration.

2. BUILDING

2.1 Pre-build

    Run Android Studio.

    Press `Start a new Android Studio project'.

    Select `Phone and Tablet` and `Basic Activity'.

    Select fields:
    Name `__PROGRAM_NAME__'.
    Package name `__PACKAGE_NAME__'.
    Language `Java'.
    Minimum SDK `API 16: Android 4.1 (Jelly Bean)'.
    Use legacy android.support libraries `empty'.

    Open the Linux console in the `__DNAME_PROGRAM__' directory.

    Run commands:

    $ git init
    $ git remote add origin git@github.com:__DNAME_GITHUB_PATH__
    $ git pull origin master
    $ ./configure
    $ make

2.2 Build

    Select menu item `Build'.

    Select submenu item `Generate Signed Bundle / APK'.

    Select radio button `APK'.

    Create the keys file. Create the password. Create the key alias.

    Select `release' and check on `Signature Versions: V1(Jar Signature)'
    and check on `Signature Versions: V2(Full APK Signature)'.

    Press next and build the application.

    Check the file in directory `__DNAME_PROGRAM__' and path `__DNAME_APP_RELEASE__/__FNAME_APP_RELEASE__' .

3. INSTALLATION

3.1 Installation through a cable

    Connect a cable to the smartphone and computer.

    Allow douwnload through the cable in the smartphone.

    Upload the apk-file to the smartphone in a directory.

    Run installation of the apk-file in the smartphone.

    Allow one installation from the untrusted source.

3.2 Installation through Internet

    Put the apk-file to an Internet service program
    (E-Mail, any messenger and etc.)

    Download this apk-file from the Internet service
    to smartphone in a directory.

    Run installation of the apk-file in the smartphone.

    Allow one installation from the untrusted source.

3.2 How to uninstall the program

Just delete the application in the smartphone or in another device.

To clean the project you can run:

    $ make clean

4. OPERATING

4.1 Run program

Search the icon of the BusSpy application in the smartphone or your
device and press the icon.

5. FILES

You can find the documentation files in the `__DNAME_BUILD__/__DNAME_BUILD_DOC__' directory.

